From 77938f1bd3420c37dbff5e5330e4bc7f66cce96b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Sep 2025 17:44:21 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:CP: wifi: ath12k: Fix vdev start freq params for 160
 MHz

The WMI command 'WMI_VDEV_START_REQUEST_CMDID' includes
frequency and width information for the channel on which the vdev is
started. There are three fields for frequency: 'mhz', 'band_center_freq1'
and 'band_center_freq2'. The 'mhz' field indicates the primary channel
frequency, while the 'band_center_freq1' and 'band_center_freq2' fields
vary based on the channel width.

For 160 MHz channel, 'band_center_freq1' should be set to the center
frequency of the primary 80 MHz segment in which the primary channel
resides, and 'band_center_freq2' should be set to the center frequency
of the entire 160 MHz channel.

But currently, 'band_center_freq1' and 'band_center_freq2' are
filled wrongly for 160 MHz channel width. 'band_center_freq1' is set to
the center frequency of the entire 160 MHz channel, and
'band_center_freq2' is set to 0.

To fix this, update the code to correctly set 'band_center_freq1'
and 'band_center_freq2' for 160 MHz channel width.

Fixes: Idd214a7c81e ("pkg upgrade Added subsys, ath11k and ath12k patches for win.wlan_host_opensource.4.0")
Patch-work: None
Patch-dependency:
ath12k/0066-wifi-ath12k-Pass-correct-values-of-center-freq1-and-.patch

Signed-off-by: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c | 9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c
index bd5904c6881f..61199fc880a0 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c
@@ -1475,7 +1475,14 @@ static void ath12k_wmi_put_wmi_channel(struct ath12k_wmi_channel_params *chan,
 
 		chan->band_center_freq2 = cpu_to_le32(arg->band_center_freq1);
 	} else if (arg->mode == MODE_11BE_EHT160) {
-		chan->band_center_freq2 = cpu_to_le32(arg->band_center_freq2);
+		if (arg->freq > center_freq1)
+			chan->band_center_freq1 =
+					cpu_to_le32(center_freq1 + 40);
+		else
+			chan->band_center_freq1 =
+					cpu_to_le32(center_freq1 - 40);
+
+		chan->band_center_freq2 = cpu_to_le32(arg->band_center_freq1);
 	} else {
 		chan->band_center_freq2 = 0;
 	}
